entries.title: As Ukraine Waits for Tanks, Europe Waits for Washington
entries.description: Fear that the U.S. could eventually dial back its support against Russia’s invasion is adding to the pressure on Europe to increase its own military and financial aid to Kyiv.

entries.title: Janet Yellen Expects EV Subsidy Rules to Prompt New Trade Deals
entries.description: The Treasury secretary says Japan and the European Union would need new pacts covering mineral sourcing for electric-vehicle batteries.

entries.title: Turkey Postpones Talks on NATO Bid by Sweden and Finland
entries.description: Decision comes after a far-right politician burned a Quran in Stockholm, drawing condemnation.

entries.title: U.S. Leans Toward Providing Abrams Tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: An announcement of tank deliveries could come this week, U.S. officials said, part of an understanding with Germany in which Berlin would agree to send its own Leopard 2 tanks.

entries.title: Ukraine's Zelensky Removes Top Officials in Bid to Contain Corruption Scandals
entries.description: The scandals, while small by the standards of previous Ukrainian governments, are a blow to the president, who has garnered praise at home and abroad for his leadership during Russia’s invasion.

entries.title: Europe's Economy Picks Up, Raising Hopes Global Recession Threat Is Receding
entries.description: Businesses in the eurozone hit the ground running in January, a further sign that the outlook for the global economy has improved.

entries.title: Russian Deaths in India Followed Days of Drinking
entries.description: The demise of Pavel Antov and Vladimir Bydanov has drawn India into international speculation over the deaths of wealthy Russians, some with ties to the Kremlin.
